tag.info:
Tags are a system of public commands that anyone can create or execute, using the BBTag language.

**Subcommands**:
{{subcommands}}

For more information about a subcommand, do `b!t help <subcommand>`
For more information about BBTag, visit <https://blargbot.xyz/tags>.
By creating a tag, you acknowledge that you agree to the Terms of Service (<https://blargbot.xyz/tags/tos>).
tag.alreadyexists: [[emote.x]] A tag with that name already exists!
tag.notag: [[emote.x]] There is no tag with that name.
tag.tagrename: [[emote.check]] The tag `{{old}}` has been renamed to `{{new}}`.

set.info: Creates or edits a tag with the provided name and content. Will not replace any tags made by anyone else.

delete.info: Deletes a tag that you own.

rename.info: Renames a tag that you own.

raw.info: Gets the raw code of a tag.

transfer.info: Transfers a tag to the specified user. Variables will not be transferred.

top.info: Displays the tags that have been the most favorited.

author.info: Displays the author of a tag.

search.info: Searches for a tag with a name containing your query.

list.info: Lists all the tags, or optionally all the tags created by a specific user.

report.info: Reports a tag for violating the ToS. Please use responsibly.

test.info: Executes the given code in a test environment.

docs.info: Gives a link to the BBTag documentation, or provides information about a specific subtag.

ccommand.info:
CCommands are a system of custom commands that moderators can create for their users, using the BBTag language.

**Subcommands**:
{{subcommands}}

For more information about a subcommand, do `b!t help <subcommand>`
For more information about BBTag, visit <https://blargbot.xyz/tags>.

set.info: Creates or edits a custom command with the provided name and content. Will not replace any tags made by anyone else.

author.info: Returns the author of the custom command.

transfer.info: Transfers ownership of a custom command to somebody else. Must be consensual.

list.info: Lists the custom commands on the guild.

test.info: Executes code in the context of your account.
